<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="a25Jul1926"><font color="red">25 July 1926</font> <i>Letters I</i> (to Harriet Weaver):  I have been for years staring at an old print of the sacrifice of Cain and Abel and it is only a week ago it struck me how tactful it was of Abel to slit the throats of the firstlings (without any divine injunction as yet to kill the Cains of the flock). However I used it in the triangle. </div>
